WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.727 --> 00:00:09.163
-[hornets buzzing]
-[screaming]

2
00:00:09.250 --> 00:00:11.078
[Stacy]
Did they sting you?

3
00:00:11.165 --> 00:00:12.123
Is it bad?

4
00:00:12.210 --> 00:00:14.386
[laughs. mutters] I'm sorry.

5
00:00:14.473 --> 00:00:16.954
People are pretty worried
y'all are gonna starve in there.

6
00:00:17.041 --> 00:00:19.217
You put this on top.
you make Indian tacos.

7
00:00:19.304 --> 00:00:22.785
You can't call it that.
It's racist.

8
00:00:22.873 --> 00:00:25.049
Girls. when someone
is trying to help you.

9
00:00:25.136 --> 00:00:26.311
it's not your place
to correct him.

10
00:00:26.398 --> 00:00:27.878
Someone should.

11
00:00:27.965 --> 00:00:30.402
What spoiled little bitches
we've raised.

12
00:00:31.098 --> 00:00:32.621
[Abigail]
They are not your children.

13
00:00:32.708 --> 00:00:34.362
You do not have the right
to speak to them that way.

14
00:00:34.449 --> 00:00:36.887
I am not talking about them.
I am talking about you!

15
00:00:36.974 --> 00:00:40.325
And your sister.
We are not on vacation!

16
00:00:40.412 --> 00:00:42.196
My husband is dead!

17
00:00:42.283 --> 00:00:44.459
 <i>Your father is dead!</i>

18
00:00:44.546 --> 00:00:47.158
[Preston] <i>Build a cabin</i>
<i>where the tents are.</i>

19
00:00:47.245 --> 00:00:49.508
 <i>and then another one with</i>
<i>a kitchen. place to gather.</i>

20
00:00:50.639 --> 00:00:53.947
[Stacy]
I want to bury him here.

21
00:00:55.079 --> 00:00:57.995
This is my home now.
I die here. too.

22
00:00:58.082 --> 00:01:00.127
♪ dramatic music ♪

23
00:01:00.214 --> 00:01:01.476
Do you know what happened
when he died?

24
00:01:01.563 --> 00:01:03.783
 <i>The whole family died with him.</i>

25
00:01:06.003 --> 00:01:08.962
♪ slow. haunting music ♪

26
00:01:37.948 --> 00:01:39.950
♪♪♪

27
00:01:58.316 --> 00:02:00.318
♪♪♪

28
00:02:10.110 --> 00:02:12.895
♪ dramatic music ♪

29
00:02:28.868 --> 00:02:30.348
Every time you leave town.

30
00:02:30.435 --> 00:02:32.306
these girls invent a crisis.
I swear to God.

31
00:02:32.393 --> 00:02:36.093
[Preston] Well. it's not
every time I leave town.

32
00:02:36.180 --> 00:02:37.703
It's every time
I go on vacation.

33
00:02:37.790 --> 00:02:40.445
If I was at a shareholder
meeting in Boston.

34
00:02:40.532 --> 00:02:42.795
everything would be just fine.

35
00:02:42.882 --> 00:02:44.666
Well. it's not fine.
and you're not here.

36
00:02:44.753 --> 00:02:47.452
Wait a minute. Hang on.

37
00:02:50.585 --> 00:02:51.934
[chuckles]

38
00:02:52.022 --> 00:02:54.285
-It's snowing. [chuckles]
<i>-Snowing?</i>

39
00:02:54.372 --> 00:02:57.244
 <i>-In June?</i>
-In June.

40
00:02:57.331 --> 00:02:58.767
 <i>What do the fish</i>
<i>think about that?</i>

41
00:02:58.854 --> 00:03:01.814
[sighs] Eh. the river's
too high to fish anyway.

42
00:03:01.901 --> 00:03:03.250
 <i>Well. then why are you...</i>

43
00:03:03.337 --> 00:03:05.948
Oh. no. never mind.
I remember.

44
00:03:06.036 --> 00:03:07.733
Cabins don't maintain
themselves.

45
00:03:07.820 --> 00:03:09.691
 <i>They sure don't.</i>[sighs]

46
00:03:09.778 --> 00:03:11.258
I can't get you
to change the curtains here.

47
00:03:11.345 --> 00:03:12.651
but you'll fly a thousand miles

48
00:03:12.738 --> 00:03:14.348
 <i>to re-stain a deck.</i>

49
00:03:14.435 --> 00:03:17.395
Well. you can change
the curtains anytime you want.

50
00:03:17.482 --> 00:03:20.528
What you can't get me to do
is have an opinion about them.

51
00:03:20.615 --> 00:03:21.834
Yeah. it's difficult
to have an argument

52
00:03:21.921 --> 00:03:23.575
when you're proving
my point. honey.

53
00:03:23.662 --> 00:03:26.404
I didn't know we were arguing.
It's been so pleasant.

54
00:03:26.491 --> 00:03:28.493
 <i>Can we get back</i>
<i>to the crisis. please?</i>

55
00:03:28.580 --> 00:03:31.844
We can talk about
whatever you want.

56
00:03:31.931 --> 00:03:33.715
 <i>So. I had lunch</i>
<i>with Abigail today.</i>

57
00:03:33.802 --> 00:03:36.153
 <i>Oh. using her full name.</i>

58
00:03:36.240 --> 00:03:38.111
Yeah. She informed me
that she and Dallas

59
00:03:38.198 --> 00:03:39.939
are getting a divorce.

60
00:03:40.026 --> 00:03:43.073
 <i>Well. I'm surprised</i>
<i>it lasted as long as it did.</i>

61
00:03:43.160 --> 00:03:44.726
It was doomed from the start.

62
00:03:44.813 --> 00:03:47.555
Well. actually. Dallas was
doomed from the start.

63
00:03:47.642 --> 00:03:50.384
Anyone who names their child
after a city.

64
00:03:50.471 --> 00:03:52.386
especially a city
they've never been to...

65
00:03:52.473 --> 00:03:54.127
 <i>You haven't heard</i>
<i>the best part.</i>

66
00:03:54.214 --> 00:03:56.869
Dallas is staying
in the apartment

67
00:03:56.956 --> 00:03:59.785
and asking for spousal support.

68
00:03:59.872 --> 00:04:01.308
[laughs] <i>Oh. yeah. well.</i>
<i>best of luck with that.</i>

69
00:04:01.395 --> 00:04:02.614
Dallas.

70
00:04:02.701 --> 00:04:04.442
All right.
where's Abby staying?

71
00:04:04.529 --> 00:04:08.098
 <i>Well. she would like</i>
<i>to speak to you about that.</i>

72
00:04:09.099 --> 00:04:10.622
I think it's time

73
00:04:10.709 --> 00:04:13.364
that we let her figure
things out for herself.

74
00:04:13.451 --> 00:04:16.976
Honey. I'm afraid
that time has passed.

75
00:04:17.063 --> 00:04:18.847
We throw her out
to sink or swim.

76
00:04:18.934 --> 00:04:21.328
we're just drowning
her kids with her.

77
00:04:21.415 --> 00:04:24.984
 <i>I don't know. Just thinking</i>
<i>about when we were young and</i>

78
00:04:25.071 --> 00:04:27.595
crammed into a shoebox
of an apartment

79
00:04:27.682 --> 00:04:30.816
with no furniture.
rationing ramen noodles.

80
00:04:30.903 --> 00:04:32.557
 <i>Ah. the good old days.</i>

81
00:04:32.644 --> 00:04:35.429
Yeah. they were. I mean.
what would you trade them for?

82
00:04:35.516 --> 00:04:37.388
Apartment with heat
might've been nice.

83
00:04:37.475 --> 00:04:39.085
 <i>No. I mean it.</i>
<i>I mean. if you had had</i>

84
00:04:39.172 --> 00:04:41.522
parents that you could run to
every time life got hard.

85
00:04:41.609 --> 00:04:43.176
would you be the man
you are today?

86
00:04:43.263 --> 00:04:45.918
 <i>Probably not.</i>
<i>but Abby isn't a man.</i>

87
00:04:46.005 --> 00:04:49.226
Wh... Whoa. wait.
what's that supposed to mean?

88
00:04:49.313 --> 00:04:51.793
 <i>Easy. I'm not</i>
<i>picking a fight here.</i>

89
00:04:51.880 --> 00:04:53.882
Yeah. well.
you let me decide that.

90
00:04:53.969 --> 00:04:57.625
Paige could handle it.
She'd find a way.

91
00:04:57.712 --> 00:05:01.194
But Abby just doesn't have it
in her. honey. She's a dreamer.

92
00:05:01.281 --> 00:05:04.458
Big dreams with absolutely
no drive to see 'em through.

93
00:05:04.545 --> 00:05:07.853
 <i>And if we had remained poor.</i>
<i>that would not have changed.</i>

94
00:05:07.940 --> 00:05:09.768
So. I don't--
What are you saying?

95
00:05:09.855 --> 00:05:12.553
 <i>She gets to remain a child</i>
<i>for the rest of her life?</i>

96
00:05:12.640 --> 00:05:14.903
She remains our responsibility

97
00:05:14.990 --> 00:05:16.470
because she does not have
the belief

98
00:05:16.557 --> 00:05:18.864
to be responsible for herself.
She never has.

99
00:05:18.951 --> 00:05:21.693
No. the word you mean
is "discipline."

100
00:05:21.780 --> 00:05:24.957
 <i>No. honey. I mean "belief."</i>
<i>You got to have that first.</i>

101
00:05:25.044 --> 00:05:26.654
[chuckles]
How can you have discipline

102
00:05:26.741 --> 00:05:28.178
about realizing a dream

103
00:05:28.265 --> 00:05:30.397
you don't believe
you're capable of achieving?

104
00:05:30.484 --> 00:05:33.313
We can love her
all we want. honey.

105
00:05:34.314 --> 00:05:36.751
We will never
make her love herself.

106
00:05:36.838 --> 00:05:41.495
[sighs] You are ruining my plan
to blame this on us.

107
00:05:42.540 --> 00:05:45.804
Yeah. don't be too hard
on her. honey.

108
00:05:45.891 --> 00:05:49.024
She's hard enough on herself.
and that's her problem.

109
00:05:49.111 --> 00:05:52.202
 <i>She's the only one</i>
<i>who can fix it.</i>

110
00:05:52.289 --> 00:05:54.291
♪ emotional music ♪

111
00:06:01.167 --> 00:06:03.213
[birds singing]

112
00:06:15.747 --> 00:06:17.052
[sighs]

113
00:06:22.884 --> 00:06:25.800
[chuckles] That's in...
that's incredible.

114
00:06:25.887 --> 00:06:27.846
Sausage or pancakes?

115
00:06:27.933 --> 00:06:29.413
-Both.
-Both.

116
00:06:29.500 --> 00:06:30.805
Since when did my girls
develop an appetite?

117
00:06:32.851 --> 00:06:35.593
-Do you want breakfast?
-What are my options?

118
00:06:35.680 --> 00:06:36.985
[Abigail]
Elk sausage or pancakes.

119
00:06:37.072 --> 00:06:38.204
Oh. God.

120
00:06:38.291 --> 00:06:39.553
[Abigail]
It's quite the quandary.

121
00:06:39.640 --> 00:06:41.338
Embrace your inner carnivore

122
00:06:41.425 --> 00:06:43.165
or face the gluten monster.

123
00:06:43.253 --> 00:06:44.471
I don't know when you became

124
00:06:44.558 --> 00:06:45.777
Miss <i>Little House</i>
<i>on the Prairie.</i>

125
00:06:45.864 --> 00:06:47.561
you juice-fasting
fucking hypocrite.

126
00:06:47.648 --> 00:06:50.129
Hey. Are you out of your mind?

127
00:06:50.216 --> 00:06:52.262
Do not talk like that
around my girls.

128
00:06:52.349 --> 00:06:54.220
Oh. your girls.
Like you own them.

129
00:06:54.307 --> 00:06:56.788
[Russell] Babe. you got to try
this baking soda stuff.

130
00:06:56.875 --> 00:06:58.877
Look at my...

131
00:07:01.445 --> 00:07:03.273
I'm gonna go for a walk.

132
00:07:03.360 --> 00:07:04.448
Take my girls. would you?

133
00:07:04.535 --> 00:07:06.667
Can we go after breakfast?

134
00:07:06.754 --> 00:07:08.147
You can go now.

135
00:07:09.757 --> 00:07:11.324
[door opens]

136
00:07:11.411 --> 00:07:13.021
Come on.

137
00:07:13.108 --> 00:07:15.110
[door closes]

138
00:07:15.197 --> 00:07:17.852
Ooh. I'm in for it now.
What are you gonna do. Abby?

139
00:07:17.939 --> 00:07:19.027
Are you gonna
bend me over your...

140
00:07:19.114 --> 00:07:21.116
[Abigail grunts]
Don't you ever

141
00:07:21.203 --> 00:07:22.988
talk like that
around my g-- Ah!

142
00:07:23.075 --> 00:07:24.816
Don't you ever
fucking touch me!

143
00:07:29.560 --> 00:07:31.257
[screams]

144
00:07:34.347 --> 00:07:35.435
[screams]

145
00:07:45.837 --> 00:07:47.099
[yells]

146
00:07:47.186 --> 00:07:49.101
[screaming]

147
00:07:52.713 --> 00:07:54.759
You girls want
to see a tantrum?

148
00:07:54.846 --> 00:07:56.413
'Cause. boy. are you going to.

149
00:07:56.500 --> 00:07:58.893
I can see that we've all

150
00:07:58.980 --> 00:08:01.461
completely forgotten
why we're here.

151
00:08:01.548 --> 00:08:05.509
Or maybe it's just that
I did such a terrible job

152
00:08:05.596 --> 00:08:07.641
as a mother
that I instilled in you

153
00:08:07.728 --> 00:08:11.079
absolutely no love or respect

154
00:08:11.166 --> 00:08:13.517
for each other or for
anyone else. for that matter.

155
00:08:13.604 --> 00:08:16.128
This is not your house.

156
00:08:16.215 --> 00:08:17.912
This is my house.

157
00:08:17.999 --> 00:08:20.350
And unlike my other house...

158
00:08:21.960 --> 00:08:24.441
...you make a mess in this one.

159
00:08:24.528 --> 00:08:26.312
you will clean it the fuck up.

160
00:08:31.970 --> 00:08:33.972
[both panting]

161
00:08:39.020 --> 00:08:41.196
Cade? Stacy.

162
00:08:42.372 --> 00:08:43.721
I'm sorry to bother you.

163
00:08:43.808 --> 00:08:46.419
but I need to pick up
Paul's truck

164
00:08:46.506 --> 00:08:48.508
at the sheriff's. and. um.

165
00:08:48.595 --> 00:08:49.770
I was wondering...

166
00:08:50.771 --> 00:08:51.772
Are you sure?

167
00:08:52.817 --> 00:08:53.818
Thank you.

168
00:08:57.125 --> 00:09:00.041
I have to say.
it is refreshing to see you two

169
00:09:00.128 --> 00:09:03.828
passionate about something.
even if it is hating each other.

170
00:09:03.915 --> 00:09:07.048
Now. if I could just
get you to show

171
00:09:07.135 --> 00:09:09.224
half this much emotion

172
00:09:09.311 --> 00:09:11.096
over losing your father.

173
00:09:11.183 --> 00:09:13.490
♪ somber music ♪

174
00:09:14.795 --> 00:09:17.015
I'll sweep. You want to mop?

175
00:09:18.103 --> 00:09:20.322
[sniffles] Yeah.

176
00:09:20.410 --> 00:09:21.976
[sighs]

177
00:09:22.063 --> 00:09:23.674
Start with the table and dishes?

178
00:09:35.990 --> 00:09:37.209
[sighs]

179
00:09:38.819 --> 00:09:40.212
[exhales]

180
00:09:40.299 --> 00:09:41.561
Everything okay?

181
00:09:41.648 --> 00:09:43.998
[Stacy sighs]
No.

182
00:09:44.085 --> 00:09:45.913
Russell. I wouldn't say so.

183
00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:47.393
What happened?

184
00:09:47.480 --> 00:09:49.700
Oh. a lot of emotions. Russell.

185
00:09:49.787 --> 00:09:51.310
They have no idea
where to put them.

186
00:09:51.397 --> 00:09:53.225
I'd give them some space

187
00:09:53.312 --> 00:09:55.662
so they don't try
to put them on you.

188
00:09:55.749 --> 00:09:58.186
Yes. I've. uh.
I've experienced that.

189
00:10:00.058 --> 00:10:02.277
It's not pleasant.

190
00:10:24.256 --> 00:10:25.257
[Bridgett]
There you go.

191
00:10:26.780 --> 00:10:27.912
Wow.

192
00:10:27.999 --> 00:10:29.740
Right?

193
00:10:29.827 --> 00:10:32.177
A real-life man cave.

194
00:10:32.264 --> 00:10:34.440
How do they get
all of this stuff up ladders?

195
00:10:34.527 --> 00:10:36.007
[Macy]
Isn't this cool?

196
00:10:36.094 --> 00:10:37.617
I don't know if
we should be up here. girls.

197
00:10:37.704 --> 00:10:39.489
I don't know how stable
the floor is.

198
00:10:39.576 --> 00:10:41.186
It's stable enough
for a pool table.

199
00:10:42.230 --> 00:10:44.755
-Well...
-What's this?

200
00:10:46.539 --> 00:10:49.716
[Russell]
Uh. well. that's. uh. like

201
00:10:49.803 --> 00:10:52.719
an antique computer game.
sort of.

202
00:10:52.806 --> 00:10:54.591
From. like. the Old West?

203
00:10:54.678 --> 00:10:56.070
From...

204
00:10:56.157 --> 00:10:59.378
Well. not from the new West.
that's for sure.

205
00:10:59.465 --> 00:11:02.555
[vehicle approaching]

206
00:11:22.923 --> 00:11:23.924
[engine shuts off]

207
00:11:25.099 --> 00:11:26.318
Thank you.

208
00:11:28.799 --> 00:11:30.235
Hmm. Maybe they should've

209
00:11:30.322 --> 00:11:31.932
beat the shit out of each other
years ago.

210
00:11:32.019 --> 00:11:34.935
Abby. I want you
to come with me.

211
00:11:35.022 --> 00:11:37.895
Paige. you keep an eye
on the girls. a close eye.

212
00:11:37.982 --> 00:11:39.244
Yes. ma'am.

213
00:11:41.942 --> 00:11:44.945
Grab that card your girls made
for the neighbors.

214
00:11:55.739 --> 00:11:57.654
[Cade mutters]
Oh. God.

215
00:11:57.741 --> 00:11:59.351
Thank you for doing this.

216
00:11:59.438 --> 00:12:03.050
Of course. Uh. excuse the mess.
It's a work truck.

217
00:12:03.137 --> 00:12:05.009
No. we're no stranger to messes.

218
00:12:05.096 --> 00:12:06.793
Then you'll be right at home.

219
00:12:08.316 --> 00:12:09.448
Oh. sorry.

220
00:12:09.535 --> 00:12:11.537
-[clattering]
-Come on.

221
00:12:13.147 --> 00:12:14.192
Yeah.

222
00:12:17.804 --> 00:12:18.849
-[Stacy] Thank you.
-[Cade] Yeah.

223
00:12:18.936 --> 00:12:21.025
[engine starts]

224
00:12:21.112 --> 00:12:23.114
♪ dramatic music ♪

225
00:12:39.217 --> 00:12:43.917
I have something for you
from my girls to say thank you.

226
00:12:44.004 --> 00:12:46.050
Oh. don't thank me.
I-I didn't do anything.

227
00:12:46.137 --> 00:12:48.966
But my wife
will be tickled pink.

228
00:12:49.053 --> 00:12:51.490
We can drop it off
if you got time?

229
00:12:51.577 --> 00:12:53.013
We have time.

230
00:13:12.903 --> 00:13:14.731
[dog barks]

231
00:13:22.782 --> 00:13:25.306
-Hey. darling.
-[Cade] Hey. mama.

232
00:13:25.393 --> 00:13:26.743
Hope y'all are gonna
put him to work.

233
00:13:26.830 --> 00:13:29.267
This one's like a cow dog.

234
00:13:29.354 --> 00:13:30.747
Obeys much better
when he's tired.

235
00:13:30.834 --> 00:13:32.749
We'll see
what we can come up with.

236
00:13:32.836 --> 00:13:34.533
My girls made this for you.

237
00:13:34.620 --> 00:13:36.796
It's silly. but they wanted
to thank you for the food.

238
00:13:36.883 --> 00:13:39.712
Well. nothing silly
about it at all. Thank you.

239
00:13:39.799 --> 00:13:42.280
How'd you like
those Indian tacos?

240
00:13:42.367 --> 00:13:43.847
Those are usually
the hit of the picnic.

241
00:13:44.935 --> 00:13:46.719
We are saving those for last.

242
00:13:46.806 --> 00:13:48.416
That's what we do.

243
00:13:48.503 --> 00:13:51.332
Cade says we got a daughter
same age as yours.

244
00:13:51.419 --> 00:13:53.160
Love to get 'em together.

245
00:13:53.247 --> 00:13:54.858
Uh. yeah. I mean. I don't know
how long we're gonna stay.

246
00:13:54.945 --> 00:13:56.468
-but we should--
-That would be great.

247
00:13:56.555 --> 00:13:58.949
-How's the school here?
-[Kestrel chuckles]

248
00:13:59.036 --> 00:14:01.299
Like the old days.
they're all crammed in one room.

249
00:14:01.386 --> 00:14:03.605
It's great for the young ones
'cause the older kids help 'em.

250
00:14:03.693 --> 00:14:05.129
And it's great
for the older ones

251
00:14:05.216 --> 00:14:06.957
-'cause they learn how to help.
-Mm-hmm.

252
00:14:07.044 --> 00:14:08.959
I'll be back before supper.

253
00:14:09.046 --> 00:14:11.613
[Kestrel]
No rush. I ain't going nowhere.

254
00:14:11.701 --> 00:14:14.355
♪ dramatic music ♪

255
00:14:14.442 --> 00:14:15.356
[Abigail]
Bye.

256
00:14:15.443 --> 00:14:16.444
[Cade]
Love you.

257
00:14:31.982 --> 00:14:33.723
So how'd you two meet?

258
00:14:33.810 --> 00:14:36.073
A rodeo.

259
00:14:36.160 --> 00:14:38.336
I was riding broncs
'cause I'm stupid.

260
00:14:38.423 --> 00:14:40.120
and she was running barrel

261
00:14:40.207 --> 00:14:42.122
'cause she's wilder
than a rabid hare.

262
00:14:46.474 --> 00:14:48.738
[whispers] I have no idea
what he just said.

263
00:14:50.261 --> 00:14:52.524
I think he's saying
they were made for each other.

264
00:14:52.611 --> 00:14:55.701
Yes. ma'am.
That's what I was saying.

265
00:15:15.460 --> 00:15:17.549
Sorry.

266
00:15:17.636 --> 00:15:20.073
Oh. That's okay.

267
00:15:22.902 --> 00:15:25.470
[Abigail sighs]

268
00:15:25.557 --> 00:15:27.559
[Cade]
Howdy. amigo.

269
00:15:29.691 --> 00:15:31.868
You still got that yellow
with the three socks?

270
00:15:31.955 --> 00:15:34.174
[Cade] No. I got him.
I ain't sure you want him.

271
00:15:34.261 --> 00:15:35.741
He's. he's fine outside.

272
00:15:35.828 --> 00:15:37.917
but he's a dancing sucker
in the box.

273
00:15:38.004 --> 00:15:39.527
He-he don't like them arenas.

274
00:15:39.614 --> 00:15:42.661
-Can I come try him?
-Yeah. anytime you want.

275
00:15:42.748 --> 00:15:44.445
I'll come over this weekend.

276
00:15:44.532 --> 00:15:46.447
[Cade] And don't bring beer.
My wife will kill us both.

277
00:15:46.534 --> 00:15:47.927
I make no promises.

278
00:15:49.668 --> 00:15:50.843
May I ask you something?

279
00:15:52.453 --> 00:15:54.194
Yes. ma'am.

280
00:15:54.281 --> 00:15:56.762
What in the world
were you two talking about?

281
00:15:56.849 --> 00:15:58.677
A horse.

282
00:15:58.764 --> 00:16:00.418
A dancing horse?

283
00:16:01.593 --> 00:16:02.681
That he is.

284
00:16:04.030 --> 00:16:05.466
Okay.

285
00:16:10.689 --> 00:16:12.822
I just need to make a copy
of the death certificate.

286
00:16:12.909 --> 00:16:13.823
[quietly]
Okay.

287
00:16:15.128 --> 00:16:17.130
The funeral home
should have prepared...

288
00:16:17.217 --> 00:16:19.089
Oh. Um...

289
00:16:24.834 --> 00:16:26.748
Oh. sorry.

290
00:16:26.836 --> 00:16:30.883
Uh. this one's the wrong one.

291
00:16:39.022 --> 00:16:41.938
♪ somber music ♪

292
00:16:45.332 --> 00:16:47.465
[copy machine whirring]

293
00:16:55.865 --> 00:16:57.605
We moved it out front for you.

294
00:16:57.692 --> 00:16:59.912
Thank you.

295
00:16:59.999 --> 00:17:02.132
We're praying for you.
Mrs. Clyburn.

296
00:17:03.176 --> 00:17:05.309
Praying? For what?

297
00:17:05.396 --> 00:17:06.745
For peace.

298
00:17:06.832 --> 00:17:07.877
It's not working.

299
00:17:14.622 --> 00:17:15.928
[truck horn honks]

300
00:17:16.015 --> 00:17:18.365
[dog barking in distance]

301
00:17:21.325 --> 00:17:23.631
[birds chirping]

302
00:17:54.619 --> 00:17:56.099
[sighs softly]

303
00:18:05.282 --> 00:18:07.110
[console opens]

304
00:18:14.465 --> 00:18:16.510
-[truck door opens]
-[console closes]

305
00:18:20.906 --> 00:18:22.125
You want me to tell him to go?

306
00:18:32.874 --> 00:18:35.703
We got it from here.
but thank you.

307
00:18:35.790 --> 00:18:36.922
[Cade]
Y'all know the way?

308
00:18:37.009 --> 00:18:38.184
Just pull it up on my phone.

309
00:18:38.271 --> 00:18:39.751
That sounds like a no.

310
00:18:39.838 --> 00:18:41.666
Uh. why don't you follow me?

311
00:18:41.753 --> 00:18:43.276
Okay.

312
00:18:45.713 --> 00:18:48.890
[engine starts]

313
00:18:58.596 --> 00:19:00.598
♪ tense piano music ♪

314
00:19:16.092 --> 00:19:17.484
[Abigail]
<i>Boy. they sure make men</i>

315
00:19:17.571 --> 00:19:19.660
different out here. don't they?
[chuckles]

316
00:19:19.747 --> 00:19:22.663
[sighs] Your father's
the only real man you ever met.

317
00:19:22.750 --> 00:19:26.232
so I'm not sure you have the
data to make that comparison.

318
00:19:26.319 --> 00:19:27.755
Okay. you know what?

319
00:19:27.842 --> 00:19:30.845
This tough love shit
is 20 years too late.

320
00:19:30.932 --> 00:19:31.977
Isn't that the truth?

321
00:19:33.544 --> 00:19:35.154
Is that why
you asked me to come?

322
00:19:35.241 --> 00:19:37.504
You didn't get it out
of your system this morning?

323
00:19:37.591 --> 00:19:39.593
Okay. you know what?
Fine. Mom.

324
00:19:39.680 --> 00:19:41.726
Pull over.
give me your best shot.

325
00:19:41.813 --> 00:19:42.944
What is your plan?

326
00:19:43.032 --> 00:19:45.077
-My plan?
-Yeah.

327
00:19:46.165 --> 00:19:48.733
In New York. for the future.

328
00:19:48.820 --> 00:19:50.996
I don't know.
co-parent my daughters?

329
00:19:51.083 --> 00:19:53.955
You're doing that anywhere.

330
00:19:54.043 --> 00:19:55.957
Work on myself?

331
00:19:56.045 --> 00:19:58.003
Honey. what does that mean?

332
00:19:58.090 --> 00:19:59.178
I don't know.

333
00:19:59.265 --> 00:20:01.876
Try and find happiness.

334
00:20:01.963 --> 00:20:04.053
Find someone who makes me happy.

335
00:20:04.140 --> 00:20:06.620
I don't know. Start dating?

336
00:20:06.707 --> 00:20:10.102
-I don't know. I'll try to--
-[sighs] You have no idea.

337
00:20:11.451 --> 00:20:12.800
No.

338
00:20:12.887 --> 00:20:15.412
-You should stay with me.
-[laughing]

339
00:20:15.499 --> 00:20:18.371
No. I am not moving
to the Upper East Side

340
00:20:18.458 --> 00:20:19.590
where everyone is married and--

341
00:20:19.677 --> 00:20:21.505
-No. no. no. I mean here.
-Here?

342
00:20:21.592 --> 00:20:22.767
I told you what I'm doing.

343
00:20:22.854 --> 00:20:24.334
-Mom.
-Abby.

344
00:20:24.421 --> 00:20:26.249
you have never been challenged
in your life.

345
00:20:26.336 --> 00:20:27.554
-[sighs] Mom.
-This would be a challenge.

346
00:20:27.641 --> 00:20:28.947
Mom. stop. Stop.

347
00:20:29.034 --> 00:20:30.644
And challenge
is exactly what you need.

348
00:20:30.731 --> 00:20:32.298
You are not moving to Montana
with no running water.

349
00:20:32.385 --> 00:20:34.213
We have running water.
We have no sewage.

350
00:20:34.300 --> 00:20:36.694
How can you live here?
You have no friends.

351
00:20:36.781 --> 00:20:38.087
The grocery store
is an hour away.

352
00:20:38.174 --> 00:20:39.436
and what are you gonna do
in the winter?

353
00:20:39.523 --> 00:20:41.002
Are you gonna chop wood?

354
00:20:41.090 --> 00:20:44.093
I know you are hurting.
We are all hurting.

355
00:20:44.180 --> 00:20:46.138
I don't know how to move on
from a failed marriage.

356
00:20:46.225 --> 00:20:49.054
I can't fathom moving on
from a perfect one.

357
00:20:49.141 --> 00:20:51.970
but this is not moving on.

358
00:20:52.057 --> 00:20:53.537
This is hiding.

359
00:20:53.624 --> 00:20:55.669
You have countless friends
in New York.

360
00:20:55.756 --> 00:20:57.323
Your family is there.

361
00:20:57.410 --> 00:20:59.325
All of the charities
that you worked so hard--

362
00:20:59.412 --> 00:21:02.198
The debate about
what I will do is over.

363
00:21:02.285 --> 00:21:05.592
This is a debate
about what you will do

364
00:21:05.679 --> 00:21:08.421
and what I will do as a result.

365
00:21:08.508 --> 00:21:11.381
I will sell your house.
which is my house.

366
00:21:11.468 --> 00:21:13.339
and as executor of the trust.

367
00:21:13.426 --> 00:21:15.776
I will cease
all payments to you.

368
00:21:15.863 --> 00:21:18.649
You want to live in New York?
You make it work.

369
00:21:20.172 --> 00:21:21.956
And what about my children?

370
00:21:22.043 --> 00:21:23.567
Pick a boarding school.
I'll pay for that.

371
00:21:23.654 --> 00:21:24.916
Yeah. and their father
needs to be

372
00:21:25.003 --> 00:21:25.960
-a part of this decision.
-Oh. no. no. no.

373
00:21:26.047 --> 00:21:27.440
I am selling his house. too.

374
00:21:27.527 --> 00:21:29.834
There are no more free rides
for anyone.

375
00:21:29.921 --> 00:21:32.880
Your options are:
stay here with me

376
00:21:32.967 --> 00:21:36.188
or you figure out
your life on your own.

377
00:21:38.234 --> 00:21:40.453
What the fuck did I do

378
00:21:40.540 --> 00:21:43.195
to make you hate me
so much. Mom?

379
00:21:43.282 --> 00:21:46.285
Abby. you don't understand that

380
00:21:46.372 --> 00:21:50.420
this is the most love
I have ever shown you.

381
00:21:50.507 --> 00:21:54.075
[sniffles]
Let me out of this car.

382
00:21:54.163 --> 00:21:58.210
I want out of this fucking car.
I want out of this fucking car!

383
00:21:58.297 --> 00:22:01.082
[tires screech]

384
00:22:02.214 --> 00:22:03.650
[screams]

385
00:22:10.048 --> 00:22:13.399
What the fuck?
What the fuck?!

386
00:22:14.661 --> 00:22:16.315
Fuck.

387
00:22:21.146 --> 00:22:22.974
Hey. bud. you busy?

388
00:22:23.061 --> 00:22:24.758
Yeah. I got some
lost cargo on 89.

389
00:22:24.845 --> 00:22:26.847
You mind running it up
to the house?

390
00:22:28.414 --> 00:22:31.287
Thanks. amigo. Yeah.

391
00:22:33.680 --> 00:22:35.204
[sighs]

392
00:22:35.291 --> 00:22:36.683
[Russell]
A big one.

393
00:22:36.770 --> 00:22:38.250
[laughter]

394
00:22:38.337 --> 00:22:39.512
[Paige]
There is a greenroom for him

395
00:22:39.599 --> 00:22:40.774
just outside the theater.

396
00:22:40.861 --> 00:22:42.994
and the screening ends at 8:52.

397
00:22:43.081 --> 00:22:44.778
and then we'll escort him out
for the Q and A.

398
00:22:44.865 --> 00:22:47.128
which is scheduled
for 25 minutes.

399
00:22:47.216 --> 00:22:50.306
[chuckles] If he wants
to do photos. he can.

400
00:22:50.393 --> 00:22:52.177
Um. and then we'll get him
over to the Soho House

401
00:22:52.264 --> 00:22:53.222
for the reception.

402
00:22:53.309 --> 00:22:55.528
[Russell and Macy laughing]

403
00:22:55.615 --> 00:22:56.921
No. I won't.

404
00:22:57.008 --> 00:23:00.272
I've had a.
a death in the family.

405
00:23:02.274 --> 00:23:03.319
Thank you.

406
00:23:10.108 --> 00:23:11.762
-Hey. you hit it.
-Come on.

407
00:23:12.806 --> 00:23:14.112
Is it cold?

408
00:23:14.199 --> 00:23:15.331
[Macy]
It feels great.

409
00:23:24.905 --> 00:23:25.993
Ooh. it's cold.

410
00:23:34.088 --> 00:23:36.439
[laughs]

411
00:23:36.526 --> 00:23:39.311
[sighing]
Relief. thank God.

412
00:23:41.792 --> 00:23:43.097
[chuckles]

413
00:23:43.184 --> 00:23:44.185
All right. come on.

414
00:23:44.273 --> 00:23:45.665
Go ahead.

415
00:23:45.752 --> 00:23:47.537
Maybe three.

416
00:23:59.766 --> 00:24:02.987
♪ dramatic music ♪

417
00:24:33.844 --> 00:24:35.976
[sniffles]

418
00:24:47.640 --> 00:24:50.382
[sobbing]

419
00:24:56.910 --> 00:24:58.608
[sighs deeply]

420
00:25:00.436 --> 00:25:01.350
[knock on window]

421
00:25:01.437 --> 00:25:03.090
Oh. God.

422
00:25:15.407 --> 00:25:19.455
That sure is a permanent
solution to a temporary problem.

423
00:25:21.805 --> 00:25:23.894
[stammers]
I'm...

424
00:25:23.981 --> 00:25:26.375
I'm not... I'm not...

425
00:25:28.333 --> 00:25:31.510
You know I got some experience
with that solution?

426
00:25:33.338 --> 00:25:35.471
My father chose it.

427
00:25:38.517 --> 00:25:41.955
Thing about suicide no one
talks about is that it's...

428
00:25:42.042 --> 00:25:45.481
-contagious. you know?
-[sighs]

429
00:25:45.568 --> 00:25:47.961
Lost a brother and an uncle
before it was through with us.

430
00:25:48.048 --> 00:25:50.921
I would never. I just...

431
00:25:52.488 --> 00:25:54.141
[stammers]

432
00:25:54.228 --> 00:25:56.666
[chuckling] My girls
would never survive without me.

433
00:25:56.753 --> 00:25:58.711
They barely survive now.

434
00:26:02.498 --> 00:26:06.197
Those things come in real handy
when you. uh. surprise a bear.

435
00:26:06.284 --> 00:26:07.677
but that's about
all they're good for.

436
00:26:07.764 --> 00:26:08.852
Yeah.

437
00:26:10.201 --> 00:26:12.943
How would you feel about me
hanging on to that

438
00:26:13.030 --> 00:26:16.686
until a grizzly
makes you real angry?

439
00:26:19.253 --> 00:26:20.603
Okay.

440
00:26:26.522 --> 00:26:28.872
When my father died. the...

441
00:26:28.959 --> 00:26:33.050
thing that surprised me the most
was all the damn paperwork.

442
00:26:34.617 --> 00:26:37.576
The paperwork has-has got to be
somebody else's job.

443
00:26:37.663 --> 00:26:39.012
Yeah.

444
00:26:40.405 --> 00:26:43.060
Your job is just to miss him.

445
00:26:44.453 --> 00:26:45.584
Yeah.

446
00:26:47.586 --> 00:26:49.066
I'll follow you this time.

447
00:26:49.153 --> 00:26:52.112
You... stay on 287
till you get to your road.

448
00:26:52.199 --> 00:26:53.897
Okay.

449
00:26:55.464 --> 00:26:56.943
Thank you.

450
00:26:57.030 --> 00:26:59.032
[rolling up window]

451
00:27:01.121 --> 00:27:03.297
[sighs]

452
00:27:03.384 --> 00:27:06.475
♪ melancholy music ♪

453
00:27:20.227 --> 00:27:23.143
[indistinct chatter]

454
00:27:23.230 --> 00:27:25.668
-[phone buzzing]
-But I just...

455
00:27:25.755 --> 00:27:27.408
Um...

456
00:27:29.585 --> 00:27:32.501
Hi. honey. Hold on just one
second. okay? I'm going outside.

457
00:27:34.198 --> 00:27:37.810
Are you okay? I have been
calling and texting. and I...

458
00:27:37.897 --> 00:27:39.159
[Stacy over phone]
<i>Are you my friend?</i>

459
00:27:39.246 --> 00:27:42.075
Am I...?
Stacy. of course.

460
00:27:42.162 --> 00:27:45.252
Think real hard
before you answer.

461
00:27:45.339 --> 00:27:48.125
Stacy. you are my best friend.

462
00:27:49.169 --> 00:27:52.042
Get on a plane. I need you.

463
00:27:52.129 --> 00:27:53.522
 <i>You text me the address.</i>
<i>and I will be there</i>

464
00:27:53.609 --> 00:27:55.088
 <i>first thing in the morning.</i>

465
00:27:58.222 --> 00:27:59.702
[inhales deeply]

466
00:28:00.877 --> 00:28:02.574
[exhales]

467
00:28:10.147 --> 00:28:12.976
No.
[scoffs]

468
00:28:13.063 --> 00:28:17.720
Is there any way someone could
bring the rental car to me?

469
00:28:18.721 --> 00:28:20.897
I will drive them back.

470
00:28:21.941 --> 00:28:23.987
Okay. you know what?

471
00:28:24.074 --> 00:28:26.598
How about I pay
for two rental cars.

472
00:28:26.685 --> 00:28:29.427
and one person follows
the other person to me?

473
00:28:33.562 --> 00:28:34.867
You know what?

474
00:28:34.954 --> 00:28:36.956
Let's try this again.
How about...?

475
00:28:37.043 --> 00:28:38.218
[siren wails]

476
00:28:40.264 --> 00:28:41.700
Uh. one second.

477
00:28:43.528 --> 00:28:44.616
This ain't very safe.

478
00:28:44.703 --> 00:28:46.183
You don't say.

479
00:28:46.270 --> 00:28:48.359
Also ain't very legal.

480
00:28:48.446 --> 00:28:50.274
Would you mind arresting me?

481
00:28:50.361 --> 00:28:51.971
Is there any way
that you can bring a rental car

482
00:28:52.058 --> 00:28:53.277
to the police station?

483
00:28:53.364 --> 00:28:54.931
Is that possible?

484
00:28:55.018 --> 00:28:56.889
Uh. I got an idea
that's a little less traumatic.

485
00:28:56.976 --> 00:28:58.499
How about I give you a ride?

486
00:29:00.023 --> 00:29:01.851
-You'd do that?
-Yes. ma'am.

487
00:29:04.810 --> 00:29:05.985
In the back?

488
00:29:06.072 --> 00:29:07.813
Only if you start
making trouble.

489
00:29:07.900 --> 00:29:10.990
I have all of today's trouble
out of my system.

490
00:29:11.077 --> 00:29:13.863
That's good news for both of us.

491
00:29:18.868 --> 00:29:20.086
Thanks.

492
00:29:25.701 --> 00:29:27.398
[Van]
<i>You're out by the Mason Ranch?</i>

493
00:29:27.485 --> 00:29:28.921
Am I?

494
00:29:29.008 --> 00:29:30.488
Where Cade works?
[sighs]

495
00:29:30.575 --> 00:29:32.664
Oh. Yes. Cade.

496
00:29:32.751 --> 00:29:34.492
Cade the cowboy.

497
00:29:34.579 --> 00:29:36.276
He is that.

498
00:29:36.363 --> 00:29:38.235
Everybody knows everybody
here. huh?

499
00:29:38.322 --> 00:29:39.758
Well. ain't much
of an accomplishment.

500
00:29:39.845 --> 00:29:41.194
[laughing]

501
00:29:43.414 --> 00:29:45.808
Oh. man.

502
00:29:50.029 --> 00:29:52.336
[crying]

503
00:29:54.294 --> 00:29:58.472
[laughing]
I'm sorry.

504
00:30:00.300 --> 00:30:01.824
If it's any consolation.

505
00:30:01.911 --> 00:30:04.522
you are seeing me
at the lowest point in my life.

506
00:30:07.003 --> 00:30:09.658
Don't get to meet many
at their best moments. ma'am.

507
00:30:09.745 --> 00:30:11.311
[Abigail sighs]

508
00:30:11.398 --> 00:30:12.878
That just ain't the job.

509
00:30:14.488 --> 00:30:15.968
I'll tell you this.

510
00:30:16.055 --> 00:30:19.015
if I had a loved one pass
in New York City...

511
00:30:20.233 --> 00:30:21.974
...I'd be a lot more lost
than you.

512
00:30:22.061 --> 00:30:23.497
[sighs]

513
00:30:26.936 --> 00:30:29.068
Do you have any music
in this thing?

514
00:30:29.155 --> 00:30:30.983
[chuckles]

515
00:30:31.070 --> 00:30:32.811
Music is the one thing
it don't have.

516
00:30:35.248 --> 00:30:37.033
But I can turn the sirens on.

517
00:30:37.120 --> 00:30:39.600
drive like a bat out of hell
if it'll make you feel better.

518
00:30:42.821 --> 00:30:43.909
It's worth a shot.

519
00:30:45.345 --> 00:30:46.782
[siren wailing]

520
00:30:58.402 --> 00:31:00.230
Boy. people just get right out
of the way. don't they?

521
00:31:00.317 --> 00:31:01.840
Yeah. sirens have that effect.

522
00:31:05.801 --> 00:31:07.890
I don't think I have the moral
compass for this kind of power.

523
00:31:07.977 --> 00:31:09.587
[laughs]

524
00:31:09.674 --> 00:31:11.110
What's your name?

525
00:31:12.503 --> 00:31:13.591
Abby.

526
00:31:13.678 --> 00:31:15.854
You're all right. Abby.

527
00:31:20.163 --> 00:31:22.165
♪ majestic music ♪

528
00:31:33.132 --> 00:31:36.135
[Russell]
Hey. we could. uh. try the. um.

529
00:31:36.222 --> 00:31:38.790
Indigenous tacos.
What do you think?

530
00:31:38.877 --> 00:31:39.965
Did we eat all the lasagna?

531
00:31:40.052 --> 00:31:41.575
Yeah. Lasagna is down.

532
00:31:41.662 --> 00:31:43.403
What's in the freezer?

533
00:31:43.490 --> 00:31:45.362
Um...

534
00:31:45.449 --> 00:31:47.103
Everything in the freezer
has hooves.

535
00:31:47.190 --> 00:31:49.714
All right.
let's try the taco things.

536
00:31:50.715 --> 00:31:51.760
[clears throat]

537
00:31:53.196 --> 00:31:54.284
Where's Mom?

538
00:31:54.371 --> 00:31:56.329
Uh...

539
00:31:56.416 --> 00:31:58.505
There's a light on in her cabin.

540
00:32:08.472 --> 00:32:10.430
I'll be back.

541
00:32:10.517 --> 00:32:12.128
[Russell]
Take bear spray.

542
00:32:12.215 --> 00:32:14.652
If there was a bear.
I think I would see it.

543
00:32:16.001 --> 00:32:18.525
[door closes]

544
00:32:18.612 --> 00:32:20.789
-[Russell clears throat]
-[door opens]

545
00:32:27.447 --> 00:32:28.884
[chuckles]

546
00:32:30.276 --> 00:32:32.757
[line ringing]

547
00:32:37.544 --> 00:32:39.590
[Abigail over recording]
<i>Hey. it's Abby. Leave a message.</i>

548
00:32:39.677 --> 00:32:40.852
[phone beeps]

549
00:32:42.071 --> 00:32:43.072
[Paige]
Mom.

550
00:32:44.900 --> 00:32:46.292
You didn't tell us
you were back.

551
00:32:46.379 --> 00:32:47.816
[Stacy sighs]

552
00:32:48.860 --> 00:32:50.862
I'm gonna have to go back out
and find your sister.

553
00:32:50.949 --> 00:32:53.125
She's at the neighbors'.

554
00:32:53.212 --> 00:32:54.126
What neighbors?

555
00:32:54.213 --> 00:32:55.606
The cowboy.

556
00:32:55.693 --> 00:32:57.913
That doesn't make any sense.

557
00:32:58.000 --> 00:32:59.523
The cowboy followed me here.

558
00:32:59.610 --> 00:33:01.873
[scoffs]
That's where she is.

559
00:33:01.960 --> 00:33:03.657
We're making dinner.
Are you hungry?

560
00:33:03.744 --> 00:33:05.137
How did she manage that?

561
00:33:05.224 --> 00:33:09.446
I heard "handsome"
and I heard "uniform."

562
00:33:11.927 --> 00:33:13.624
What's for dinner?

563
00:33:13.711 --> 00:33:16.757
The tacos.
We dare not speak their name.

564
00:33:16.845 --> 00:33:20.544
I cannot wait for those girls
to meet the woman who made them.

565
00:33:24.113 --> 00:33:26.202
We swam in the river today.

566
00:33:26.289 --> 00:33:27.638
Oh. yeah? How was that?

567
00:33:27.725 --> 00:33:29.379
Felt great on my hoo-ha.

568
00:33:29.466 --> 00:33:30.946
[laughing]

569
00:33:31.033 --> 00:33:33.513
And then Russell made me
this baking soda bandage.

570
00:33:33.600 --> 00:33:35.951
There's no telling the yeast
infection I'm in store for.

571
00:33:36.038 --> 00:33:37.735
but the swelling is sure down.

572
00:33:37.822 --> 00:33:38.954
My vagina is
almost back to normal.

573
00:33:39.041 --> 00:33:39.955
Jesus.

574
00:33:40.042 --> 00:33:41.347
I got to say. Paige.

575
00:33:41.434 --> 00:33:44.133
not the answer I was expecting.

576
00:33:44.220 --> 00:33:46.135
[sizzling]

577
00:33:46.222 --> 00:33:47.701
[door opens]

578
00:33:48.746 --> 00:33:50.443
What are you doing. girls?

579
00:33:50.530 --> 00:33:51.880
Found this in our cabin.

580
00:33:51.967 --> 00:33:53.925
Internet stopped working.

581
00:33:54.012 --> 00:33:56.754
♪ gentle music ♪

582
00:34:00.976 --> 00:34:03.674
[Bridgett] So. why'd you
throw Mom out of your truck?

583
00:34:03.761 --> 00:34:05.110
[chuckles]

584
00:34:05.197 --> 00:34:06.982
-For beating Paige's ass?
-[Paige] Hey.

585
00:34:07.069 --> 00:34:10.811
Number one. it was a draw.
Number two. nice language.

586
00:34:10.899 --> 00:34:15.294
I didn't. Your mother asked
to get out of the truck.

587
00:34:15.381 --> 00:34:16.992
Not what she said.

588
00:34:17.079 --> 00:34:19.516
Well. her relationship
with the truth remains the same.

589
00:34:20.604 --> 00:34:23.476
Okay. I think this is ready.

590
00:34:40.450 --> 00:34:42.539
♪ bright. uplifting music ♪

591
00:35:06.389 --> 00:35:07.738
-[dog barks]
-[Kestrel] Tony...

592
00:35:07.825 --> 00:35:10.132
don't rope the dog.

593
00:35:13.483 --> 00:35:14.397
And what are you doing?

594
00:35:14.484 --> 00:35:16.529
-Making a spear.
-Hey.

595
00:35:16.616 --> 00:35:17.748
a little help here?

596
00:35:17.835 --> 00:35:20.098
Hey. boys!
[whistles]

597
00:35:21.273 --> 00:35:23.754
-[Kestrel] Here you go. darling.
-Oh. thank you.

598
00:35:23.841 --> 00:35:25.234
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

599
00:35:25.321 --> 00:35:26.626
Don't got to ask them twice.

600
00:35:26.713 --> 00:35:27.976
[Cade]
Thanks. mama.

601
00:35:28.063 --> 00:35:29.803
[Kestrel]
You're welcome.

602
00:35:31.066 --> 00:35:32.719
Swap leads into the turn. Kayla.

603
00:35:42.555 --> 00:35:44.557
[whispers indistinctly]

604
00:35:48.866 --> 00:35:51.564
[clears throat] Looks like
you're about out of horse.

605
00:35:51.651 --> 00:35:54.089
Let's...
get her washed up and fed.

606
00:35:54.176 --> 00:35:56.047
Oof.

607
00:35:56.134 --> 00:35:59.094
Well. don't mind us
while we herd wild children.

608
00:36:03.750 --> 00:36:05.665
-Oh. my God.
-[Kestrel] Spade. uh-uh.

609
00:36:05.752 --> 00:36:07.972
Let that snake go.
He's not bothering you.

610
00:36:08.059 --> 00:36:10.322
[Abigail] Are there more
of those things around?

611
00:36:10.409 --> 00:36:12.585
Oh. you want as many
of those around as you can get.

612
00:36:12.672 --> 00:36:14.674
[chuckles]
Why is that?

613
00:36:14.761 --> 00:36:16.372
[Van]
Keep the rodents away.

614
00:36:16.459 --> 00:36:18.548
If you ain't got rodents.
you ain't got rattlesnakes.

615
00:36:19.723 --> 00:36:21.159
-Good to know.
-[Van] Mm.

616
00:36:23.466 --> 00:36:27.600
Uh. looks like they're...
Should we go?

617
00:36:27.687 --> 00:36:30.038
Oh. they'll get those kids
put down. be right back out.

618
00:36:31.691 --> 00:36:34.216
Oh. thanks. You have kids?

619
00:36:34.303 --> 00:36:35.956
Two boys.

620
00:36:36.044 --> 00:36:37.262
How old?

621
00:36:37.349 --> 00:36:38.611
Fourteen and 11.

622
00:36:40.613 --> 00:36:43.616
I was the scourge of New York
when I got pregnant at 20.

623
00:36:43.703 --> 00:36:45.836
Oh. You fit right in here.

624
00:36:47.098 --> 00:36:48.099
Where's your wife?

625
00:36:49.144 --> 00:36:50.580
Oh. she died.

626
00:36:52.669 --> 00:36:54.279
-I'm sorry.
-No. it was. uh.

627
00:36:54.366 --> 00:36:57.152
it was a few years ago.

628
00:37:01.460 --> 00:37:03.071
Cancer?

629
00:37:03.158 --> 00:37:05.856
An ATV flipped over on her.

630
00:37:05.943 --> 00:37:09.599
She was... running it up a hill
she had no business being on.

631
00:37:09.686 --> 00:37:12.341
but you couldn't tell her no.

632
00:37:14.647 --> 00:37:16.519
She was wild as fire.

633
00:37:21.045 --> 00:37:23.308
-What about you?
-Mm.

634
00:37:23.395 --> 00:37:27.965
My ex-husband is...
very much alive.

635
00:37:28.052 --> 00:37:29.749
I only wish he were dead.

636
00:37:31.403 --> 00:37:32.839
You don't wish that.

637
00:37:32.926 --> 00:37:34.145
[chuckles]
I'm just... I'm kidding. I'm...

638
00:37:34.232 --> 00:37:36.016
I shouldn't have said that.
I was...

639
00:37:37.888 --> 00:37:39.237
He a good father?

640
00:37:42.153 --> 00:37:43.720
That's an interesting question.

641
00:37:43.807 --> 00:37:46.201
Well. pretty important one.
He's half the deal.

642
00:37:46.288 --> 00:37:48.725
Just interesting
you thought to ask it.

643
00:37:50.770 --> 00:37:52.816
What's interesting is...

644
00:37:55.471 --> 00:37:56.950
...you haven't answered.

645
00:38:00.519 --> 00:38:04.088
Hope he is. For your kids' sake.

646
00:38:07.396 --> 00:38:09.528
It's getting late.

647
00:38:09.615 --> 00:38:10.660
Want me to take you home?

648
00:38:10.747 --> 00:38:13.358
Oh. I would like that very much.

649
00:38:13.445 --> 00:38:16.231
but for now I will settle
for the ranch next door.

650
00:38:18.363 --> 00:38:21.366
Well. ranch next door it is.

651
00:38:21.453 --> 00:38:23.151
[grunts]

652
00:38:24.152 --> 00:38:25.370
Thanks.

653
00:38:34.162 --> 00:38:35.380
What?

654
00:38:36.729 --> 00:38:38.035
What what?

655
00:38:39.123 --> 00:38:40.298
[chuckles]
What are you...?

656
00:38:40.385 --> 00:38:42.213
Well. you want to go back.
right?

657
00:38:42.300 --> 00:38:43.910
-Yeah.
-Okay.

658
00:38:43.997 --> 00:38:46.565
-But you're not walking.
-I'm waiting for you.

659
00:38:46.652 --> 00:38:49.481
Oh. You want me to move first.

660
00:38:49.568 --> 00:38:51.483
And then I walk with you.
That's how it works.

661
00:38:51.570 --> 00:38:53.485
Okay. Yeah. Just...

662
00:38:53.572 --> 00:38:55.879
Still figuring out
the rules here. so...

663
00:38:55.966 --> 00:38:57.489
They ain't too hard
to figure out.

664
00:38:57.576 --> 00:38:58.795
Yeah.

665
00:38:59.883 --> 00:39:02.625
-[clears throat]
-[opens gate]

666
00:39:05.367 --> 00:39:07.064
-Thanks.
-You bet.

667
00:39:08.065 --> 00:39:10.110
♪ gentle music ♪

668
00:39:15.725 --> 00:39:18.249
[engine starts]

669
00:39:34.309 --> 00:39:36.398
♪♪♪

670
00:40:02.815 --> 00:40:04.904
♪♪♪

671
00:40:10.388 --> 00:40:12.477
[Abigail]
Oh. thanks.

672
00:40:19.745 --> 00:40:21.965
How long are you in the valley?

673
00:40:22.052 --> 00:40:26.056
That is the question.
and I have no answer.

674
00:40:26.143 --> 00:40:29.538
Oh. Here's another one.
When are y'all coming back?

675
00:40:29.625 --> 00:40:32.454
Another question with no answer.
[chuckles]

676
00:40:33.716 --> 00:40:34.934
Why?

677
00:40:36.980 --> 00:40:38.155
Why do you ask?

678
00:40:40.288 --> 00:40:41.550
I know you're dealing
with a lot.

679
00:40:41.637 --> 00:40:43.203
and this. this ain't the time--

680
00:40:43.291 --> 00:40:46.032
Good timing is not something
I was blessed with.

681
00:40:46.119 --> 00:40:47.599
Got to take my shots
when they come.

682
00:40:51.516 --> 00:40:53.083
I'm trying to decipher that.

683
00:40:53.170 --> 00:40:56.695
There's not much to decipher.
The answer is yes.

684
00:40:57.783 --> 00:40:59.350
I ain't asked a question yet.

685
00:41:01.439 --> 00:41:03.049
Answer's still yes.

686
00:41:05.922 --> 00:41:07.315
Okay.

687
00:41:07.402 --> 00:41:09.360
This is when
the country boy thing

688
00:41:09.447 --> 00:41:11.580
needs a little kick in the ass.
Do you have a pen?

689
00:41:11.667 --> 00:41:14.713
-Uh. yeah. [chuckles]
-Something to write on?

690
00:41:17.716 --> 00:41:18.717
[Van mumbles]

691
00:41:27.683 --> 00:41:30.120
Right. okay. so I'll. uh...

692
00:41:33.950 --> 00:41:35.691
Great.

693
00:41:37.475 --> 00:41:39.825
Nope. I'm gonna. I'm gonna
need one more of those.

694
00:41:53.839 --> 00:41:56.276
-Oh. my God.
-[laughs]

695
00:41:56.364 --> 00:41:57.452
Okay.

696
00:41:58.888 --> 00:42:00.803
You better go.

697
00:42:00.890 --> 00:42:02.674
or I'm gonna drag you
into a horse stall.

698
00:42:04.067 --> 00:42:06.765
That's not the threat
to make me leave.

699
00:42:07.984 --> 00:42:09.507
Um...

700
00:42:11.683 --> 00:42:14.382
I am gonna go-- thank you--

701
00:42:14.469 --> 00:42:17.254
do damage control
on my daughters.

702
00:42:17.341 --> 00:42:20.518
After we plot out a cemetery
and plan a funeral.

703
00:42:20.605 --> 00:42:24.870
I am pretty free.
so give me a call.

704
00:42:24.957 --> 00:42:28.047
[chuckles] I'll do it.
[clears throat]

705
00:42:36.012 --> 00:42:38.406
Oh. my God.
he's fucking beautiful.

706
00:42:38.493 --> 00:42:40.843
[Russell] I don't know
about beautiful. He's fit.

707
00:42:40.930 --> 00:42:43.889
He's in shape. but that's. like.
the job. you know. so. please.

708
00:42:43.976 --> 00:42:45.238
He's so cute. Mom.

709
00:42:45.325 --> 00:42:47.023
-Really?
-Yeah.

710
00:42:47.110 --> 00:42:48.807
You just found him
on the street?

711
00:42:48.894 --> 00:42:50.374
-Well. actually. he found me.
-[Paige] It was steamy.

712
00:42:50.461 --> 00:42:51.854
-[giggles]
-What are you guys doing?

713
00:42:51.941 --> 00:42:53.377
[Paige]
Sexy man.

714
00:42:53.464 --> 00:42:55.423
[laughter and indistinct chatter
inside house]

715
00:42:56.467 --> 00:42:58.426
♪ uplifting music ♪

716
00:43:01.733 --> 00:43:03.518
[Stacy moans]

717
00:43:03.605 --> 00:43:06.651
[Preston]
That doesn't hurt?

718
00:43:06.738 --> 00:43:08.174
Harder.

719
00:43:08.261 --> 00:43:10.873
Your threshold for pain
should be studied.

720
00:43:10.960 --> 00:43:12.396
Walk 30 blocks
in four-inch heels.

721
00:43:12.483 --> 00:43:15.312
then tell me it's
the foot massage that hurts.

722
00:43:15.399 --> 00:43:17.532
I'm gonna take your word for it.

723
00:43:17.619 --> 00:43:21.666
So. the judge didn't award
spousal support

724
00:43:21.753 --> 00:43:23.059
or child support.

725
00:43:23.146 --> 00:43:26.192
Why would he?
They're both unemployed.

726
00:43:26.279 --> 00:43:28.238
Says each parent
is responsible for expenses

727
00:43:28.325 --> 00:43:30.327
when they have the girls.

728
00:43:30.414 --> 00:43:32.721
And they need to split tuition.

729
00:43:33.765 --> 00:43:36.899
Or. I don't know.
place them in public school.

730
00:43:36.986 --> 00:43:38.683
[scoffs]
That's not happening.

731
00:43:38.770 --> 00:43:40.119
Well. maybe it should happen.

732
00:43:40.206 --> 00:43:42.034
In the Village?
Come on. honey. Look.

733
00:43:42.121 --> 00:43:45.037
this is a win because the court
isn't dictating what we do.

734
00:43:45.124 --> 00:43:46.648
We're just gonna have
to cover the gap

735
00:43:46.735 --> 00:43:48.084
when the girls are with him.

736
00:43:48.171 --> 00:43:50.347
He hasn't worked
a day in his life.

737
00:43:50.434 --> 00:43:52.436
-[sighs]
-If we don't help.

738
00:43:52.523 --> 00:43:55.483
he'll tuck tail and go.
Who knows?

739
00:43:55.570 --> 00:43:58.224
Where do
35-year-old adolescents go?

740
00:43:58.311 --> 00:44:01.793
Oh. Los Angeles.
Try to become a fucking actor.

741
00:44:01.880 --> 00:44:03.752
[chuckles]

742
00:44:03.839 --> 00:44:06.015
Then we're just robbing
their children.

743
00:44:06.102 --> 00:44:07.756
He's a nice guy.

744
00:44:07.843 --> 00:44:11.542
He's a dilettante with
zero ambition. but he's nice.

745
00:44:12.587 --> 00:44:14.719
That's partly our fault.
We did. We...

746
00:44:14.806 --> 00:44:16.765
we enabled it.

747
00:44:16.852 --> 00:44:18.201
You're enabling it now.

748
00:44:18.288 --> 00:44:20.682
If we're always around
to pick her up.

749
00:44:20.769 --> 00:44:23.423
she's never gonna learn
to stand on her own.

750
00:44:23.511 --> 00:44:26.862
For God's sake.
she's 33 years old.

751
00:44:27.950 --> 00:44:29.517
We need to let her fall down.

752
00:44:32.650 --> 00:44:35.871
Honey. I-I can't do that.
[chuckles]

753
00:44:35.958 --> 00:44:38.395
She may be the oldest.
but she's still my baby.

754
00:44:38.482 --> 00:44:40.702
And I can't.
[stammers]

755
00:44:40.789 --> 00:44:42.442
I can't take that risk.

756
00:44:42.530 --> 00:44:45.402
Picking her up when she falls...

757
00:44:46.969 --> 00:44:49.275
...is my job.

758
00:44:49.362 --> 00:44:51.408
♪ gentle music ♪

759
00:44:57.675 --> 00:45:00.504
[laughter inside house]

760
00:45:05.857 --> 00:45:07.467
Told you. honey.

761
00:45:27.313 --> 00:45:29.751
♪ dramatic music ♪
